Knapsack - Class in Unnamed Package
Static class designed to solve the knapsack problem:
Take a set of values, determine which combination of those values is the greatest without going over a given limit
Knapsack() - Constructor for class Knapsack
 
knapsackOutput(String, int[], int, int) - Static method in class Knapsack
Runs knapsackSum() with the given parameters and generates a String output (for the knapsackSum() method with a List parameter).
knapsackOutputNoList(String, int[], int, int) - Static method in class Knapsack
Runs knapsackSum() with the given parameters and generates a String output (for the knapsackSum() method without a List parameter - will NOT include the list of values used, just the final sum).
knapsackSum(int[], int, int) - Static method in class Knapsack
Calculates the largest combination of values in array w that is smaller than the given limit
knapsackSum(int[], int, int, List<Integer>) - Static method in class Knapsack
Calculates the largest combination of values in array w that is smaller than the given limit Adds the values used into the given List
